Explaination: you are given an array and a target , find the least length sub set in the array which  sums up to the target.


Algorithm:

Step 1: If array length == 0 return 0;
Step 2: left left , sum , minLength be 0;
Step 3: start the for loop with right = 0 and goes up to the length of the input array:
                  sum = sum + current index of the input array
                  when sum >= target:
                        we compute min length  =  min(minlength, right - left +1
                         remove the left most number from the window from the sum and increment the left element
Step 4: Return the minLength



Code:
class Solution {
    public int minSubArrayLen(int target, int[] nums) {

        if(nums.length == 0) return 0;

        int left =0;
        int num = 0;
        int sum = 0;
        int minLength = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for(int right =0 ; right < nums.length; right++)
        {
            sum += nums[right];

            while(sum >= target)
            {
                minLength = Math.min(minLength, right - left +1);

                sum -= nums[left];
                left++;
            }
        }
        
        return minLength == Integer.MAX_VALUE ? 0 : minLength;
    }
}
